<p><img src=\"http://farm5.static.flickr.com/4101/5057918556_ddb2857a0f.jpg\"/></p>
<p>So what has the Right learnt from this? That there is not enough <a href=\"http://www.naomiklein.org/shock-doctrine\" target=\"_blank\">disaster capitalism</a>. There is <a href=\"http://www.unitedliberty.org/articles/7083-the-free-market-didnt-let-the-house-burn\" target=\"_blank\">inadequate greed</a>. </p>" "http://chinamieville.net/post/1256845843" (19628 49308) new 12 nil nil ((title nil "Lessons from an unnecessary conflagration") (description nil "<p>The <a href=\"http://www.wpsdlocal6.com/news/local/Firefighters-watch-as-home-burns-to-the-ground-104052668.html\" target=\"_blank\">unfuckingbelievably macabre barbarisms</a> of the market occasionally lead to a <a href=\"http://thelede.blogs.nytimes.com/2010/10/06/tennessee-firefighters-watch-home-burn/\" target=\"_blank\">tiny bit</a> of disquiet.</p>
